Hey! i have a question. Recently i've been noticing some bio-compostible bags with label "plastic free" are they actually environmental friendly?

@mussie_11 the ones that are made of starch are compostable. But the problem is, these when segregated might end up in recycling unit instead of getting composted and will cause problem in recycling as they are not plastic. So, its best to avoid both plastic and starch bags. Compost your kitchen waste and collect dry waste as it is or in a paper bag.
